This paper deals with the economics of personal mobile data and user behavior, which falls under the category of Cybersecurity (cs.CR) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The study also involves data analysis and interpretation, which could be categorized under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the implications for the design of mobile services, which could be classified under Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CY).
